-- House Panel Adds $146 Million for 8 United Technologies Choppers
-- B y   T o n y   C a p a c c i o
-- 2013-06-11T17:05:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-11/house-panel-adds-146-million-for-8-united-technologies-choppers.html
The House panel responsible for
defense expenditures plans to approve a $98.3 billion weapons
request for fiscal 2014 that adds money for Blackhawk
helicopters made by  United Technologies Corp. (UTX)  and Patriot
missile interceptors from  Lockheed Martin Corp. (LMT)   The additions to the Pentagon’s budget request are
contained in the House Appropriations defense subcommittee’s
draft report posted on its website today. The full
appropriations committee will meet tomorrow to approve the
weapons request that’s part of a $512 billion annual defense
budget plan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Capaccio in Washington at 
 acapaccio@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Liebert at 
 lliebert@bloomberg.net  